{"TopicId":211430,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How do i orbit?","CreatedByName":"NewKSPPlyer","CreatedById":224772,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-11T03:38:05Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"NewKSPPlyer","CreatedById":224772,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-11T03:38:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey, I am new and i wanna learn how to properly kerbal in ksp, can anyone help me orbit?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-11T05:25:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s a thing I made a while back. Haven\u0027t updated it for some time but should still work.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002227914\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8162129460\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/115750-how-to-reach-orbit-and-a-sandbox-rocket-to-do-it-with/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, welcome to the forum. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EAlso, thread moved to the Gameplay Questions sub.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-11T07:41:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOrbiting is easy! Just miss the ground while you fall back from space \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E(And no, I\u0027m not joking, that\u0027s literally what an orbit is. Gravity will always pull you back down, but if you go sideways fast enough, you can avoid hitting the planet and keep curving around it.)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mahnarch","CreatedById":114432,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-16T17:00:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224217876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022211430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221673422887\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298962\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Streetwind\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/11/2023 at 2:41 AM, Streetwind said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOrbiting is easy! Just miss the ground while you fall back from space \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E(And no, I\u0027m not joking, that\u0027s literally what an orbit is. Gravity will always pull you back down, but if you go sideways fast enough, you can avoid hitting the planet and keep curving around it.)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe opposite of what Nelson Muntz would say: \u0022Stop not hitting yourself! Stop not hitting yourself!\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022sddefault.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lAUNlO6-rlk/sddefault.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}